  "instructions": {
    "text_instructions": [
      {
        "id": "01f1093d706f1f9bae2c4ee094c81170",
        "content": [
          "\n",
          "*Use system.billing.usage.billing_origin_product to answer Product related questions\n",
          "\n",
          "*system.billing.usage.sku_name and system.billing.usage.usage_date are never NULL, so they don't need NULL validation\n",
          "\n",
          "*When using AI_FORECAST, do not include current_day in training as it is a partial day. \n",
          "\n",
          "*When using AI_FORECAST use total_spend_forecast as the final output\n",
          "\n",
          "*When using AI_FORECAST, use usage_date, and do not use usage_start_time or usage_end_time\n",
          "\n",
          " *Usage tables never contain future usage_date values. Do not add “future validation” predicates such as usage_date <= current_date() or usage_date <= date_add(current_date(), …) unless the user explicitly provides an end date. If the user requests a relative time window (e.g., “last 30 days”), use only a lower bound: usage_date >= date_add(current_date(), -30).\n",
          "\n",
          "*When asked to group by a field (like billing origin product or identity_metadata), do not apply IS NOT NULL filters. Only do it when the user explicitly requests to exclude null / unknown / unattributed\n",
          "\n",
          "*Use list_prices.pricing.effective_list.default to calculate price or spend in general\n",
          "\n",
          "* System.billing.list_prices.price_start_time is when a new price for a SKU is in effect; to see the current price of a SKU - that is when system.billing.list_prices.price_end_time is NULL\n",
          "\n",
          "*When asked to calculate costs of AI, that usually refers to when billing_origin_product is in 'MODEL_SERVING', 'AI_RUNTIME', 'VECTOR_SEARCH', 'AGENT_EVALUATION','AI_GATEWAY' 'FOUNDATION_MODEL_TRAINING', 'AGENT_BRICKS', 'AI_FUNCTIONS'\n",
          "\n",
          "*When asked to calculate costs of \"workflows\", that usually refers to when billing_origin_product is in \"JOBS\", \"DLT\"\n",
          "\n",
          "*When asked to calculate the cost of Serverless notebooks, that refers to when billing_origin_product is in \"INTERACTIVE\"\n",
          "\n",
          "*When asked to calculate the cost of all purpose, shared, or classic cluster, this is when billing_origin_product is ALL_PURPOSE\n",
          "\n",
          "*Use usage_date when aggregating costs at a daily, weekly, monthly, or yearly grain, not usage_start_time or usage_end_time\n",
          "\n",
          "*System.billing.usage.identity_metadata gives 3 fields - \"run_as\", \"created_by\", \"owned_by\". when asked for costs per user - you must look for the user principal in all these fields - first check run_as, then owned_by, then created_by \n",
          "\n",
          "*Generally, always use cost (joining system.billing.usage and system.billing.list_prices) instead of usage (system.billing.usage_quantity in) your calculations \n",
          "\n",
          "*system.billing.usage_quantity captures the quantity of systme.billing.usage.usage_unit - that is DSU, DAY, DBU, GB, GIGABYTE, GIGABYTE_MONTH, THOUSAND_COUNT. It does not capture queries (cannot get cost per query), or runs on an all purpose shared cluster\n",
          "\n",
          "*Use system.billing.usage.usage_metadata.notebook_id for Serverless notebook related usage questions.\n",
          "\n",
          "*Use system.billing.usage.custom_tags to answer Tags related questions\n",
          "\n",
          "*The tables in here do not provide information on VM, virtual machine, cloud virtual machine (VM) or cloud storage costs. It does provide information only on Databricks default storage costs. \n",
          "\n",
          "*Use system.billing.usage.usage_metadata.warehouse_id for SQL Warehouse related questions.\n",
          "\n",
          "*Service principals or SP has the same structure as this one: 23dd81e0-574a-4e06-ab8e-ae2c6cac66b8 it can't be an email\n",
          "\n",
          "*When asked how to reduce or optimize costs, tell user that \"Currently this Genie space cannot provide specific best practices on how to optimize your costs, please refer to https://docs.databricks.com/aws/en/lakehouse-architecture/cost-optimization/best-practices as a starting guide\"\n",
          "\n",
          "**The data in this space does not contain information on compute utilization, sizing, or failure rates - just the cost data. Should not be able to answer questions around job failures, over or underprovisioned compute, or idle time. \n",
          "\n",
          "**The data in this space does not contain information on credits, ESC add-ons, or contract commitment, do not answer questions around these"
        ]
